 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Notebook 14: Advanced Control and Persistence in LangGraph\n",
    "\n",
    "**🎯 Goal:** Learn how to build production-grade agentic systems by adding persistence, streaming, and human-in-the-loop workflows to your LangGraph applications."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧩 Concept Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "To move our agents from prototypes to production, we need more control over their execution. This notebook covers three critical concepts:\n",
    "\n",
t- **Persistence with Checkpoints:** What if a long-running agent crashes? Checkpoints allow you to save the state of your graph at each step. This means you can resume the graph from where it left off, making your agents fault-tolerant.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Streaming:** Instead of waiting for the final result, streaming allows you to get a real-time feed of events from your graph as they happen. You can see which node is running, what tools are being called, and what the intermediate results are. This is essential for building responsive user interfaces.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Human-in-the-loop:** Some tasks are too critical to be fully automated. This pattern allows you to pause the graph at a specific point, wait for a human to review the work and provide input or approval, and then continue."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ⚙️ Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "We will need `sqlite3` for the checkpointer."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import sqlite3\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "from typing import TypedDict, Annotated\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "\n",
    "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n",
    "from langchain_core.messages import AnyMessage, SystemMessage, HumanMessage, ToolMessage\n",
    "from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\n",
    "from langgraph.checkpoint.sqlite import SqliteSaver\n",
    "from langchain_core.tools import tool\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv()\n",
    "llm = ChatOpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Persistence with Checkpoints\n",
    "\n",
    "A checkpointer saves the state of your graph after each step. We'll use an in-memory SQLite database for this."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AgentState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    messages: Annotated[list[AnyMessage], operator.add]\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def search(query: str):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Searches for the query.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return f\"Results for '{query}': The answer is 42.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "llm_with_tools = llm.bind_tools([search])\n",
    "\n",
    "def agent_node(state, config):\n",
    "    result = llm_with_tools.invoke(state[\"messages\"])\n",
    "    return {\"messages\": [result]}\n",
    "\n",
    "# The checkpointer\n",
    "memory = SqliteSaver.from_conn_string(\":memory:\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the graph\n",
    "graph = StateGraph(AgentState)\n",
    "graph.add_node(\"agent\", agent_node)\n",
    "graph.set_entry_point(\"agent\")\n",
    "graph.add_edge(\"agent\", END)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compile the graph with the checkpointer\n",
    "persistent_app = graph.compile(checkpointer=memory)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Graph with persistence is compiled.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Resuming from a Checkpoint\n",
    "\n",
    "To resume a conversation, you just need to pass the `thread_id` of the conversation in the config."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# A unique ID for our conversation thread\n",
    "config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"my-thread-1\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run the app. The state will be saved.\n",
    "persistent_app.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"hi! my name is bob\")]}, config)\n",
    "print(\"--- First run complete ---\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run it again with the same thread_id. The model will have the history.\n",
    "response = persistent_app.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"what is my name?\")]}, config)\n",
    "print(\"--- Second run complete ---\")\n",
    "print(response['messages'][-1].content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Streaming Intermediate Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "Using `.stream()` instead of `.invoke()` lets us see what's happening inside the graph in real-time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def call_model(state):\n",
    "    return {\"messages\": [llm_with_tools.invoke(state[\"messages\"])]}\n",
    "\n",
    "def call_tool(state):\n",
    "    tool_calls = state[\"messages\"][-1].tool_calls\n",
    "    tool_outputs = []\n",
    "    for tc in tool_calls:\n",
    "        output = search.invoke(tc[\"args\"])\n",
    "        tool_outputs.append(ToolMessage(content=str(output), tool_call_id=tc['id']))\n",
    "    return {\"messages\": tool_outputs}\n",
    "\n",
    "def should_continue(state):\n",
    "    return \"action\" if state[\"messages\"][-1].tool_calls else \"end\"\n",
    "\n",
    "streaming_graph = StateGraph(AgentState)\n",
    "streaming_graph.add_node(\"agent\", call_model)\n",
    "streaming_graph.add_node(\"action\", call_tool)\n",
    "streaming_graph.set_entry_point(\"agent\")\n",
    "streaming_graph.add_conditional_edges(\"agent\", should_continue, {\"action\": \"action\", \"end\": END})\n",
    "streaming_graph.add_edge(\"action\", \"agent\")\n",
    "streaming_app = streaming_graph.compile()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Stream the events\n",
    "config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"stream-thread-1\"}}\n",
    "inputs = {\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"What is the meaning of life?\")]}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"--- Streaming Events ---\")\n",
    "for event in streaming_app.stream(inputs, config):\n",
    "    for node, output in event.items():\n",
    "        print(f\"\\nNode: {node}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"Output: {output}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Human-in-the-loop\n",
    "\n",
    "To add a human-in-the-loop step, we can add an 'interrupt' to our graph. The graph will execute up to the interrupt point, then wait. We can inspect the state, and then resume the graph's execution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We'll interrupt the graph before calling a tool\n",
    "human_in_loop_app = streaming_graph.compile(interrupt_before=[\"action\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"human-in-loop-thread\"}}\n",
    "inputs = {\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"I need to find out the answer to life.\")]}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run the app - it will pause before the 'action' node\n",
    "paused_state = human_in_loop_app.invoke(inputs, config)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"--- Graph Paused ---\")\n",
    "print(f\"Next step: {paused_state.next}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Current messages: {paused_state.values['messages'][-1].tool_calls}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# The user can now approve/deny. Here, we'll just resume it.\n",
    "print(\"\\n--- Resuming Graph ---\")\n",
    "final_result = human_in_loop_app.invoke(None, config)\n",
    "print(f\"Final result: {final_result['messages'][-1].content}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💡 Pro Tip\n",
    "\n",
    "**Streaming is the key to a good user experience** in any agentic application. Users don't want to stare at a loading spinner for 30 seconds while the agent works. Streaming tool calls, thoughts, and intermediate steps shows the user that the agent is making progress and builds trust in the system. Almost any real-world deployment of a LangGraph agent will use `.stream()` or `.astream()`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🏁 Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "You now have the tools to build robust, interactive, and production-grade AI agents.\n",
    "\n",
    "1.  **Persistence Creates Fault-Tolerance:** Checkpoints allow your agents to recover from interruptions and manage long-running tasks effectively.\n",
    "2.  **Streaming Creates a Better UX:** Use `.stream()` to provide real-time feedback to users, showing them what the agent is doing at each step.\n",
    "3.  **Human-in-the-loop Adds Safety and Control:** For critical tasks, you can pause the graph and require human approval before the agent takes its next action."
   ]
  }
 ],
